The paper discusses the signal to noise ratio in a lensless compressive imaging architecture, which involves compressive sensing and image capture in a compressed form. This topic is related to several sub-categories of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), computer vision (cs.CV), optics and photonics (cs.OE), multimedia (cs.MM), and signal processing (cs.SI). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
